&gt; Bloat is extremely common in Genetic Programming and I would suspect that it
&gt; is for the same reason as Ken mention previously - expansion of the genome
&gt; for the purpose of moving outside of local minima, ie, exploration.
&gt; 
&gt; The methods to control it there is to assign a hard limit on the size of the
&gt; tree - in this case a hard limit on maximum nodes.  I don&#39;t know if that&#39;s
&gt; such a good idea in this case as it presupposes that you know how big you
&gt; want your network.  Another method is to incorporate network complexity into
&gt; the fitness function such that you favor smaller genomes with the same
&gt; fitness.
&gt; 
&gt; -Kirk
